# Banhatten Design System - Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** React 19+ (Server Components compatible)
- **Language:** TypeScript (Strict mode)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 (Utility-first) + `class-variance-authority` (CVA)
- **Icons:** `lucide-react`
- **Repo Structure:** Turborepo Monorepo
  - `apps/docs`: Documentation (Next.js)
  - `packages/ui`: Component Library
  - `packages/tokens`: Design Tokens (JSON + Config)

## Coding Standards
- **Components:** Functional components only. Use `forwardRef` where applicable.
- **Props:** All component props must extend standard HTML attributes (e.g., `React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>`).
- **Exports:** Named exports only (e.g., `export const Button...`).
- **Utils:** Use a `cn(...)` utility for class merging (Tailwind Merge + CLSX).
- **Accessibility:** Mandatory. All interactive elements must have proper ARIA attributes.

